      • findType

        public IType findType(java.lang.String descriptor)
        This method finds and returns a type, given its name.

        The following types of types can be found:

        • Primitive Types
        • Void IType
        • Null IType
        • Previously Manufactured - Class Types
        • Previously Manufactured - Interface Types
        • Previously Manufactured - Enum Types
        • Previously Manufactured - Array Types
        • Class.forName(name)

        Specified by:
        findType in interface ITypeFactory
        Parameters:
        descriptor - is the name of the type to find.
        Returns:
        the aforedescribed type, or null, if no suitable type can be found.
